<Action id="30732" issue="20734" author="amundson" type="comment" created="2017-09-11 16:18:24.0" updateauthor="amundson" updated="2017-09-11 16:18:24.0"> <body><! CDATA Also, making sure that relevant error messages are logged in /var/log/sawtooth/validator-*-error.log such that they can be used to refer to troubleshooting/FAQ information related to the errors.  Two such example errors:  "AVR enclave quote status is not OK: GROUP_OUT_OF_DATE" --- FAQ is to update your BIOS.  "Unable to create enclave.: SGX ERROR: SGX_ERROR_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE" -- FAQ is to check the module is loaded with 'lsmod | grep isgx' and address that if it is not loaded.  (And possibly other things to check.)  ></body> </Action>
